## The winning thesis (what judges should understand instantly)

**MedGuardian = “Consent-as-code + Timeline diagnostics + Verifiable audit receipts.”**
A clinician can only run diagnosis workflows *if* the patient’s policy allows it; every run creates a **Data Use Receipt** anchored onchain; outputs are offchain but provably untampered via hashes.

This aligns perfectly with CRE’s strengths: **verifiable workflows** (consensus computing) across HTTP + EVM reads/writes. ([Chainlink Documentation][1])

